{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place all ingredients into mixing bowl and blend <nobr>15 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>, or until a dough is formed.","Divide dough into equal halves, then place one half onto a piece of baking paper. Roll into a sausage, then wrap dough in baking paper. Repeat process with remaining half of dough, then freeze both portions for a minimum 1 hour.","Preheat oven to 200°C. Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside. Slice dough into rounds (approx. 1 cm thick) and place onto prepared baking tray.","Bake for 10-12 minutes (200°C) or until golden and edges are crisp. Transfer onto a wire rack and allow to cool completely before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g butter, cut into cubes and frozen","220 g self-raising flour","100 g walnuts","150 g blue cheese, cut into pieces","2 egg yolks","1 pinch ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r89696","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-oArtF49n6as\/XZanv1diEqI\/AAAAAAAAhDg\/eXD77v_Bn1UBKdPrw2it8upKX5wmY0i_gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_TNjoa9UUH8KCn49v.png","title":"Walnut and blue cheese shortbread","publishedAt":"2015-12-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1.9 g","fat":"5.3 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"4 g","calories":"298 kJ \/ 71 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), wire rack, freezer, oven","hintsAndTricks":["These make an excellent addition to any cheese or fruit platter. They are also stunning as part of a gift hamper. Place shortbread into a wrapped box and pair with wine, cheeses and a jar of quince or apple and ginger paste."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 20m","40 pieces"]}